NAME
    Message::Passing::Redis - Produce or consume messages by Redis PubSub

SYNOPSIS
        # Terminal 1:
        $ message-passing --input STDIN --output Redis --output_options '{"topic":"foo","hostname":"127.0.0.1","port":"6379"}'
        {"data":{"some":"data"},"@metadata":"value"}

        # Terminal 2:
        $ message-passing --output STDOUT --input Redis --input_options '{"topics":["foo"],"hostname":"127.0.0.1","port":"6379"}'
        {"data":{"some":"data"},"@metadata":"value"}

DESCRIPTION
    A Redis transport for Message::Passing, allowing you to publish messages
    to, or subscribe to messages from Redis.

SEE ALSO
    Message::Passing::Input::Redis
    Message::Passing::Output::Redis

